  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.12.2\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nI got this error when running ` hh coverage`\r\n```\r\nError in plugin solidity-coverage: HardhatError: HH11: An internal invariant was violated: Invalid harfork name shanghai\r\n```\r\nit failed when compiling in the coverage plugin, and `hh compile` works fine. \r\n\r\nI think it might be due to Im using solidity-coverage `v0.8.4` (the latest version that supports new hardhat versions),\r\nBut in that case, is there a workaround to use latest solidity-coverage version without updating hardhat?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**NOTE**: open an issue cuz is the suggestion in the HH11 error doc\r\n\r\n> #[HH11: Invariant violation](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/errors#HH11)\r\nAn internal invariant was violated. This is probably caused by a programming error in hardhat or in one of the used plugins.\r\n> Please [report it](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/issues/new) to help us improve Hardhat.\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nHaven't tried it in a template project\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
